results.name: Number of added unique known entries when going from the n X n to the (n+1) X (n+1) multiplication table.
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: When going to 8 X 8, the added entries 8,16,24 are already known, so a(7)=3:
mathematica: A062854 = Table[u = If[n == 1, {}, Union[u, n Range[n]]]; Length[u], {n, 1, nmax+1}] // Differences // Prepend[#, 1]&;
xref: Unique values of sequence are in A108408.
Cf. A027424 (total unique entries), A062854 (added unique unknown entries).
